folder: St. Nicholas Avenue & 155th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
St. Nicholas Avenue (old Kingsbridge Road) at N.E. corner of 155th Street, showing houses numbered 906 to 918, adjoining the vacant corner. One of these, 906, antedates 1885; the others were built shortly after.
Early in the 1920's 906 and 908, the two nearest to the camera, will be taken down, and the block rebuilt down to the corner.
About 1912.

folder: 155th Street (West) & St. Nicholas Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
West 155th Street, between St. Nicholas and Amsterdam Avenues. Views 1,2 show the north side of the street, the house having belonged to John Whalen. View 3 shows the Whalen residence on the south side of the street.

E. P. Chrystie
March 18, 1923
Views 1-3
